IN LOCAL HISTORY
• 30 YEARS AGO — Keith Forsyth scored two goals and added a pair of assists to lead the South team to an 8-4 victory over the North in the South West Hockey League’s all-star game. Forsyth, of the Boissevain Border Kings, was named the game’s MVP.
•20 YEARS AGO — Jomar Cruz, the 18-year-old netminder, turned aside 37 of 38 shots to backstop the injury-ridden Brandon Wheat Kings to a 4-1 triumph over the WHL’s East Division-leading Prince Albert Raiders.
